(1160, 'gZpltiVF', 'Why us?', '', 1155, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>Provide a summary of the Company Name section. Here you will need to spell out all those points that favour the selection of your company in preference to the other competitors. Some of these points will include the skills and experience of your team members. In what ways are the business acumen and the industry connections better in your team mates? How do they excel in matters such as innovations or industry connections and expertise in the subject matter? What sort of professional competence do your key advisors possess? </p>', 'Why us?', 1),
(1161, 'gZpltiVF', 'Business Expectations', '', 1154, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Business Expectations', 'Business Expectations', 1),
(1162, 'gZpltiVF', 'Financial Projections', '', 1161, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>In this space you will need to make a summary of your financial goals. You will have to specify the kind of revenue you think you are likely to make within the first year of the busness. Further, you will need to mention the type of revenue growth you expect within the coming years. An important estimate you will have to provide deals with the profitability expectation for your business. How soon do you expect to break even and start making profits?You may need to specify the reason in case you plan to run your business as a loss making venture. Here, the details you will provide will also include the important metrics that would bear watching. The projected financial statements may well be seen by your readers later on. Your endeavour should be to heighten the interest of your readers to learn more in respect of your company by using this space to review the various highlights of the forecast you have prepared. </p>', 'Financial Projections', 1),
(1163, 'gZpltiVF', 'Financing Required', '', 1161, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>The section Financial Projections will need to be summarized.</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">How will you finance your business?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Will you need financing from extraneous sources or do you have adequate finances or is it already fully self sufficient? It is up to you to either remove the section or make a note in case you do not need financing from outside sources. </li></ul>', 'Financing Required', 1),
(1164, 'gZpltiVF', 'Business Opportunity', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Business Opportunity', 'Business Opportunity', 1),
(1165, 'gZpltiVF', 'Problem & Solution', '', 1164, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Problem & Solution', 'Problem & Solution', 1),
(1166, 'gZpltiVF', 'Problem worth solving', '', 1165, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>Your customers may have a key problem or a need that has not been met. If your line of business is the common type such as a beauty parlour or a restaurant, please explain as to why your customers have a need to frequent the parlour or the eating joing. Is it because your place is cheaper or because you maintain hours that are convenient to your patrons? Is your place situated at a good location or do you meet a necessity that is otherwise not available in your neck of the woods? Such an example could be a late night Latte Coffee Bar or a sandwich bar that is open till the wee hours of the night.</p>', 'Problem worth solving', 1),
(1167, 'gZpltiVF', 'Our Solution', '', 1165, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>It is possible that your business has a novel way of solving an existing problem. If this is the case please explain why, in your opinion, is this what the world requires. In what way do the existing solutions not make the grade? Please spell out the innovative nature of your solution. This can be anything from an outstanding breakthrough in medical science or just a mundane item that is common place but impressive nevertheless. This can be a method to iron clothes without the use of electricity or a non-invasive surgery for a critical medical condition. In case your company''s pitch is that it tackles diverse problems faced by the customer then you should discuss these in this space. In such a case amend the heading accordingly and call it Problems instead of Problem.</p><p>While discussing the solutions too you will need to explain clearly how your products or services plan to meet the need of your customer. In case of shortage of parking space your solution might be to offer a rental service for bikes that can be dropped off and picked up at designated spots both near where the students live and where they go to attend their classes. As in the case of Problems, in this case also you may like to reclassify the topic to the use of the plural for Solution in case your plan is to offer solutions to multiple problems.</p>', 'Our Solution', 1),
(1168, 'gZpltiVF', 'Target Market', '', 1164, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Target Market', 'Target Market', 1),
(1169, 'gZpltiVF', 'Market Size & Segments', '', 1168, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>You will now need to discuss your target customers. The questions you will need to find answers to include</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Who are your ideal customers?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Who is the target with problems whose solutions you are offering?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Is it possible to group the customers into cogent segments with respect to needs, locational areas and aspirations? </li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Your reserch should indicate approximate figures in each segment.</li></ul><p>In case you run a gymnasium downtown you may find that different sets of customers may want to use your facility at different times of the day. These sets could be the professionals, the retired people and the college students from the nearby area. Your entire solution must take cognizance of the needs and paying capacities of your customers as well as their requirements in terms of laundry services among others. </p><p>It is important to size your segments. You must assess how lucrative your business in likely to be and this will depend on your customer size in each segment and the paying capcity. If the likely income is inadequate your business might not grow. </p>', 'Market Size & Segments', 1),
(1170, 'gZpltiVF', 'Competition', '', 1164, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Competition', 'Competition', 1),
(1171, 'gZpltiVF', 'Current Alternatives', '', 1170, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>You will need to discuss the competitive environment next. Discuss the kind of competition you have, who these ompetitors are and what are the kinds of solutions they have on offer similar to your solutions. Discuss also why in your opionion the customers might select their solution. </p><p>It is also possible that you may not have any competition in your field. This is fairly common with most of the newer startup innovative companies. The old stalwarts such as Ford did not have any competitors in their field back then. Their customers used whatever state transport was available. Pioneers such as Ford and Sony had to find a way to beat the existing alternatives. Therefore, in case you do not have any competitors just yet, it will still be necessary to debate on the method or methods used by your customers to solve their problem or problems. It is being wise to acknowledge the fact that competition is around the corner even if it is not available right now. You will always need to stay ahead of the race. For this reason you must identify the various advantages you have over all your competitors or alternatives that exist in the market. You will also need to assess whether your products and services enjoy a price advantage in your competitive environment. In case this is not true then you will have to find out why your customers will opt for your solution. The next choice might well be that your solution is better or faster or that your product lasts longer or tastes better. Your outlet might be very conveniently located or your customer service might be better. It is also feasible that your offer suits a certain class of customers.</p>', 'Current Alternatives', 1),
(1172, 'gZpltiVF', 'Our Advantages', '', 1170, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>It is possible that the advantages you have are different for diverse customers. An example could be that of offering expensive notebooks bound in leather as against the cheaper and coarser paper kind available elsewhere. These will be attraxtive to the right kind of customers. When you compare the same product against tablets with software your product may appeal to customers that favour the joy of writing on paper and the absence of need for a cord and power outlet. </p>', 'Our Advantages', 1),
(1173, 'gZpltiVF', 'Execution', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Execution', 'Execution', 1),
(1174, 'gZpltiVF', 'Marketing & Sales', '', 1173, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Marketing & Sales', 'Marketing & Sales', 1),
(1175, 'gZpltiVF', 'Marketing Plan', '', 1174, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>In this space you will need to discuss your marketing plan''s components.</p><ul style=''color:#999''><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>What will be your marketing strategy for the purpose of increasing your customer base? </li><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>Will you invest in SEO, TV time or social media, radio commercial time or in email, signages and digital advertising? </li><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>Do you have or are you planning to have a logo and brand?</li></ul><p>At this stage you will need to select from the above and have estimates and ensure that your forecast includes these figures. </p><p>In case you are planning on advertising, you will need to concentrate on the message you wish to get across. What do you want your USP to be? Is is that you want to vibe with your customers? Discuss how this pitch compares with that of your competitors. Do you want your pitch to be that of a low cost option for those that are consciousof their budget? Or do you wish to project your company''s brand image of a superior product? You may also indicate to your customers that your product is of a special sort such as a solution that is eco-friendly or one that is faster, a solution that is easier and more convenient or one that is locally sourced. Of course all this must be in sync with what you have already committed in the Competitive Landscape Section.</p><p>Discuss your plans of distribution and pricing. What is the manner in which your customers will pay for your products and/or services? Will you expect them to pay at the store or in the field? Or do you want that they should pay at your website? The other options could be payment at the retailers or distribuiters or the resellers. The other point you may clarify is whether your customers are those that buy and use your products or will you sell your products to another company or companies that will include your solution along with theirs? Do you expect that your customers pay up for their purchase each time or will this be a continuous arrantement? There is obviously a fair amount to discuss in this space as can be seen. Additional topics may also be added to this section depending upon the size of your business and its complexity. In such a case it may be more convenient to simply discuss the major points in this space and only refer to all the other points for greater detail. For the smaller businesses however, one can cover all the major issues quite adequately here. </p>', 'Marketing Plan', 1),
(1176, 'gZpltiVF', 'Sales Plan', '', 1174, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>You will need to discuss the manner in which you will sell your products and/or services. It is not necessary to discuss all the activities related to marketing in this space like how you plan to attract all your customers to be. All you need to focus on is how you wish to convert all your likely customers into actuals. These likely customers are those who turn up and ask questions and request for a newsletter and those that ask you for an estimate. So, how do you plan to make all these people your customers. While this may not be too difficult a problem in the smaller businesses it may need a greater degree of working in the case of a business such as insurance or enterprise software where you will need to discuss the finer details of the sales process. In such a case you may need to talk about your staffing needs and whether you have a commission structure. You may discuss your sales territories and quotas or describe the kind of sales activities you will have to use in order to build and maintain your sales process. These may be follow up calls and emails or planning networking events and trade associations as well as referrals among others. </p>', 'Sales Plan', 1),
(1177, 'gZpltiVF', 'Business Operations', '', 1173, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Business Operations', 'Business Operations', 1),
(1178, 'gZpltiVF', 'Locations & Facilities', '', 1177, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>In this space you have to give details of the physical locations of your company. This may well be your office or the place where your store is located or the plants for manufacture or the place where you store all your products. It can be any location that is related to your business. What is the kind of total space you have and how does this relate to the present and future needs of your company? It is quite possible that location is an important factor in your kind of business that may well be a cinema hall or bowling alley or a restaurant. In such a case you will need to explain how the location benefits your business. Are you able to attract a lot of traffic or pedestrians that pass by? Is your location favourable to your target customers? Does your location make it easy for you to run your business such as if it is close to the freeway or a shipping port? Further, in case you operate from home you will need to discuss how this is working well for you or are you thinking of moving out to a new office later on? In case you are,you may give details of when and why. </p>', 'Locations & Facilities', 1),
(1179, 'gZpltiVF', 'Technology', '', 1177, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>Your business may demand the use of some software or hardware or IT tool. You may have been using these tools or may be intending to use them in the future. Please discuss these tools here.</p>', 'Technology', 1),
(1180, 'gZpltiVF', 'Milestones & Metrics', '', 1173, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Milestones & Metrics', 'Milestones & Metrics', 1),
(1181, 'gZpltiVF', 'Milestones', '', 1180, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Milestones', 0),
(1182, 'gZpltiVF', 'Key Metrics', '', 1180, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>In this space you will need to explain the performance parameters that are critical to you.</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">In your perception how do you view success?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">How will you know when you are successful?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">In your view is it critical to keep a check on the direct costs in an industry that works on low margin?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Will you consider your business to be successful if you had adequate leads that help sustain your sales pipeline to its full capacity?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Do you need to have a certain sum of money in your bank for you to feel success?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Are you looking for your website with some flow or see hits being converted into customers?</li></ul><p>Your goal should be to monitor the progress of your plan by continuously tracking the actual results so that you are able to focus on bad assumptions and poor performance quickly enough. This will give you time to do a mid-course correction so that your business remains on track. What you need to do is to find out which of the performance parameters need to be watched with care. </p>', 'Key Metrics', 1),
(1183, 'gZpltiVF', 'Company', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Company', 'Company', 1),
(1184, 'gZpltiVF', 'Overview', '', 1183, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Overview', 'Overview', 1),
(1185, 'gZpltiVF', 'Ownership & Structure', '', 1184, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>Here the specifics of the owner or owners have to be explained. While explaining multiple partnerships please mention the percentage share of each in the business. You will also need to discuss the legal structure of your company as to whether it is on the basis of a sole proprietor or it is based on a partnership in the form of a limited liability corporation. It can also be a partnership firm wherein the profits are passed on to individual partners. It can also be a non-profit company or a corporation such as the S type or the  C type with its own tax obligations. It is possible that you are only just beginning and you may not be totally familiar with all these options. In such a case please carry out an online search for various types of business structures and this will give you adequate reading material on the advantages and disadvantages of the different options.</p>', 'Ownership & Structure', 1),
(1186, 'gZpltiVF', 'Team', '', 1183, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Team', 'Team', 1),
(1187, 'gZpltiVF', 'Management Team', '', 1186, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p> For discussing the management team you will need to give the details of the team first. Thereafter, you will need to write out the skills and experience of each team member besides how they will be contributing towards the running of the company business. The details will include the ways in which the members add strength to the company. In case the members have any special qualifications or an experience in the field of interest this will be explained. This space has to be well utilised detailing your strength and that of your team members. If it is true that you have an amazing plan this is where you will show how you are the perfect person to exploit it. In case you are the sole owner of the company, you will have to discuss all your experience and skills as well as the successes you may have had in the past. You may also wish to change the name of this section so that the term of team or team members is avoided since you are the sole proprietor. </p>', 'Management Team', 1);
INSERT INTO `plan_menu` (`menuid`, `companyid`, `title`, `summary`, `parentid`, `status`, `createdby`, `createdon`, `modifiedby`, `modifiedon`, `content`, `hidden_title`, `permission`) VALUES
(1188, 'gZpltiVF', 'Advisors', '', 1186, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>In this space you will discuss all the mentors and investors as well as the professors or the experts from the industry or the subject matter besides friends who are knowledgeable and members of the family among others that have helped you in the business. Give the details of the person or group of persons who you would turn to for advice whenever you have a query or come across a new kind of challenge faced by the business. Explain also the reason why such people are a great help to you and your company. </p>', 'Advisors', 1),
(1189, 'gZpltiVF', 'Financial Plan', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Financial Plan', 'Financial Plan', 1),
(1190, 'gZpltiVF', 'Forecast', '', 1189, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Forecast', 'Forecast', 1),
(1191, 'gZpltiVF', 'Key Assumptions', '', 1190, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>Here you will need to justify the values you obtained in your financial forecast. You will need to explain whether you projected your revenue figures by basing these on your past results or market research and a good guess extrapolating from the number of people that visit your store and the percentage of these that may buy or did you use any other method? You will also need to explain the kind of growth that is being assumed, the notable expenditure and the important hires. You may also indicate the level of profit you hope to generate. It will be possible for your readers to see the details of the forecast in your plan. Please make use of this space to create the actual story behind the numbers mentioned. You may also like to indicate the manner in which the financial projections corroborate your conviction that this opportunity is a strong one that is totally deserving of your investment and time. </p>', 'Key Assumptions', 1),
(1192, 'gZpltiVF', 'Revenue', '', 1190, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Revenue', 0),
(1193, 'gZpltiVF', 'Expenses By Year', '', 1190, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Expenses By Year', 0),
(1194, 'gZpltiVF', 'Net Profit and Loss', '', 1190, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Net Profit and Loss', 0),
(1195, 'gZpltiVF', 'Financing', '', 1189, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Financing', 'Financing', 1),
(1196, 'gZpltiVF', 'Use Of funds', '', 1195, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>This space is to be used for you to explain what you propose to do with all forms of financing such as loans and investments that you might have mentioned in your forecast. You may also clarify if these will help cover all the operating costs during the process of scaling up of your new business. You may also explain if this will help finance different forms of capital expenditure that might include the purchase of new and expensive equipment. Please explain to your readers why you will need all these funds and how these will be paid off. However, in case you are not planning on seeking financing please remove this topic. </p>', 'Use Of funds', 1),
(1197, 'gZpltiVF', 'Sources of funds', '', 1195, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '<p>In this space you may please discuss your financing plans. Do you plan to invest your own money? Will you be using a credit card or a line of credit? What are the other kinds of funds do you expect to receive and when do you think you will receive these? Some of these types of funds can be in the form of either personal loan or a business loan and the equity investments that you may receive from others. It is both possible and understandable in case you do not readily have the complete details of the future financing all worked out. All you need to do is to try and explain whatever it is that you know and when you hope to be able to sort out all the details. In case financing is not being sought you may use the space above to give out your plans of bootstrapping your company that is the funding of the growth of the company from its own profits. Alternately, please remove this topic totally from the plan. </p>', 'Sources of funds', 1),
(1198, 'gZpltiVF', 'Statements', '', 1189, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 'Statements', 'Statements', 1),
(1199, 'gZpltiVF', 'Setup Cost', '', 1198, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Setup Cost', 0),
(1200, 'gZpltiVF', 'Income profit and lose', '', 1198, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Income profit and lose', 0),
(1201, 'gZpltiVF', 'Cashflow', '', 1198, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Cashflow', 0),
(1202, 'gZpltiVF', 'Balance Sheet', '', 1198, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', 29, '2016-10-17 10:58:52', '', 'Balance Sheet', 0),
(1203, 'twyPIdTU', 'Business Summary', '', 0, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Business Summary', 'Business Summary', 1),
(1204, 'twyPIdTU', 'Business Opportunity', '', 1203, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Business Opportunity', 'Business Opportunity', 1),
(1205, 'twyPIdTU', 'Problem Description', '<p class="p1">The Indian culture, often labelled as an amalgamation of several cultures, spans across the Indian subcontinent and has been influenced by a history that is several millennia old. Every Indian family understand their community and celebrates events throughout the year. With the modernization, family events have just lost the importance and people are just trying to cut down the entire process.</p><br><p class="p1">Families who are residing in urban or semi-urban areas are facing difficulty in arranging family events The current vendors which are available in the market have problems like:</p><br><p class="p1">1) Expensive</p><br><p class="p1">2) Poor product quality</p><br><p class="p1">3) No pre-defined process</p><br><p class="p1">4) False commitment on timeline</p><br><p class="p1">5) Poor Communication or sometimes messy</p><br><p class="p1">None of the platforms has overcome this problem in this space.</p>', 1204, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:16:45', '<p>Here you need to make a summary of what had been written in the Problem Statement section. The summary should consist of what all is required by your customers which they cannot find anywhere else. Your business need not be unique but you will need to specify those reasons that justify the existence of your business. It is possible that the location you have selected is excellent or your pricing has an edge over the other competitors. It is important to appreciate that only once you have addressed all the details should you attempt to write out the executive summary. </p>', 'Problem Description', 1),
(1206, 'twyPIdTU', 'The Solution', '<p class="p1">Holydelights will be a one-stop online platform for Indian families to search,plan,organize and manage any family events. Holydelights will support end-to-end event management starting with suggesting the most auspicious event timings,recommending suitable service providers or vendors and providing continuous support until the event gets executed.</p>', 1204, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:17:59', '<p>Here you will need to make a summary of whatever was written in The Solution section. The prominent questions that need to be answered are (a) What is your solution to the customer''s problems and (b) Why are your products or services so critically important for them?</p>', 'The Solution', 1),
(1207, 'twyPIdTU', 'Market Opportunity', '<p class="p1">Family events primary an unorganized market and now it is turning out to be an organized one. Event management industry in India is more than 15 years old and now it is gaining more momentum. During the late 1990s and early 2000 industry has spent around 20 + crores on diversified events.</p>\n<p class="p1">In upcoming years, it is expected to clock a growth rate of 25 % annually on YOY(Year-On-Year ).</p><p class="p1">Source: Business Insider &amp; TOI 2014 &amp; 2015 edition<br></p>', 1204, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:18:52', '<p>Make an incisive summary of Market Opportunity section. Offer a good interpretation of your idea of an ideal customer. Also specify the number of potential customers you are likely to have for the solution you have in mind. See if you can find a yardstick with which you can group your customers into discrete types. </p>', 'Market Opportunity', 1),
(1208, 'twyPIdTU', 'Competitive Landscape', '<p class="p1">We have a unique platform for online customers to search,plan and manage their family events. As of now there is no direct established company or startups exists who are competing in this space.</p>\n<p class="p1">However there are quite a few indirect players who has both online /offline mode of business :</p>\n<p class="p1">1. Wedding specific - Weddingz.in,Weddingplz.com, wedmegood.com, shaadisaga.com</p>\n<p class="p1">2. Birthday specific - evibe.in</p>\n<p class="p1">3. Event - Explara.in</p>\n<p class="p1">Generic listing portals - Urban Clap, Housejoy, Sulekha, JustDial, YellowPages.</p>', 1204, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:19:14', '<p>You will need to make a summary of what had been written in the Competitive Landscape section. Make a list of the various options that your customers have for their problems and in what way is the solutionn offered by you better than these. </p>', 'Competitive Landscape', 1),
(1209, 'twyPIdTU', 'Why us?', '<p class="p1">Holydelights portal powered by Delightz Infotech, is an e-marketplace for Service providers for conducting Family-events.</p>\n<p class="p1">Mr. Tilak Bhattacharyya is the Director-Operations for Delightz Infotech.Tilak has over twenty years of experience in the areas of IT Delivery and Consulting in the Retail and Manufacturing domains.</p>\n<p class="p1">Tilak has significant global exposure of working with some of the leading Retailers like Tesco Plc,Stop&amp;Shop and Delhaize Le Lion.Tilak with his unique blend of keen Business sense, strong Leadership skills is well placed to steer Holydelights to success.</p>\n<p class="p1">Being Bootstrapped, Delightz Infotech has opted for a cautious long-term approach.Currently, Delightz Infotech is operating with a 3-member Team (including Tilak).And hiring would happen as and when required in the coming days.</p>\n<p class="p1">The IT product development has been outsourced to a Third-party after having the required documentations in place.</p>\n<p class="p1">Holydelights (powered by Delightz Infotech) intends to provide a platform to individuals for an end to end planning and execution of Family events. Holydelights intends to bring in transparency and convenience to the entire process through the application of technology.</p>', 1204, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:25:47', '<p>Provide a summary of the Company Name section. Here you will need to spell out all those points that favour the selection of your company in preference to the other competitors. Some of these points will include the skills and experience of your team members. In what ways are the business acumen and the industry connections better in your team mates? How do they excel in matters such as innovations or industry connections and expertise in the subject matter? What sort of professional competence do your key advisors possess? </p>', 'Why us?', 1),
(1210, 'twyPIdTU', 'Business Expectations', '', 1203, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Business Expectations', 'Business Expectations', 1),
(1211, 'twyPIdTU', 'Financial Projections', '<p class="p1">Our research suggests that we can maximum onboard 250 - 300 customers in next 1 year on an average transaction of INR 20,000 which makes total revenue of INR 50 lacs. We are expected to grow at the rate 20 % - 25 % and try to touch upon the magical figure of INR 1 Cr in next 3 - 4 years.</p>', 1210, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:26:52', '<p>In this space you will need to make a summary of your financial goals. You will have to specify the kind of revenue you think you are likely to make within the first year of the busness. Further, you will need to mention the type of revenue growth you expect within the coming years. An important estimate you will have to provide deals with the profitability expectation for your business. How soon do you expect to break even and start making profits?You may need to specify the reason in case you plan to run your business as a loss making venture. Here, the details you will provide will also include the important metrics that would bear watching. The projected financial statements may well be seen by your readers later on. Your endeavour should be to heighten the interest of your readers to learn more in respect of your company by using this space to review the various highlights of the forecast you have prepared. </p>', 'Financial Projections', 1),
(1212, 'twyPIdTU', 'Financing Required', '<p class="p1">To start with, all the initial expenses will be managed internally in a typical bootstrap mode. In next 12 months, Holydelights will seek Bank Loans and Equity investment to overcome operating expenses and meet future business development activities.</p>', 1210, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:27:42', '<p>The section Financial Projections will need to be summarized.</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">How will you finance your business?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Will you need financing from extraneous sources or do you have adequate finances or is it already fully self sufficient? It is up to you to either remove the section or make a note in case you do not need financing from outside sources. </li></ul>', 'Financing Required', 1),
(1213, 'twyPIdTU', 'Business Opportunity', '', 0, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Business Opportunity', 'Business Opportunity', 1),
(1214, 'twyPIdTU', 'Problem & Solution', '', 1213, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Problem & Solution', 'Problem & Solution', 1),
(1215, 'twyPIdTU', 'Problem worth solving', '<p class="p1">The Event industry is bit segmented into various category and customer face problem to avail services from one service provider. One has to spend time &amp; cost to get services which are sometimes resulting into a big reputation loss.</p>\n<p class="p1">Online family event management sector is new from India landscape perspective. From an Indian context, Family events like Marriage, Namkaran, Grihaprabesh are something that is held across all communities. In present times where people are hard-pressed for time, customers look for established players who are capable of providing an assured outcome at a pre-defined cost.</p>', 1214, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:28:58', '<p>Your customers may have a key problem or a need that has not been met. If your line of business is the common type such as a beauty parlour or a restaurant, please explain as to why your customers have a need to frequent the parlour or the eating joing. Is it because your place is cheaper or because you maintain hours that are convenient to your patrons? Is your place situated at a good location or do you meet a necessity that is otherwise not available in your neck of the woods? Such an example could be a late night Latte Coffee Bar or a sandwich bar that is open till the wee hours of the night.</p>', 'Problem worth solving', 1),
(1216, 'twyPIdTU', 'Our Solution', '<p class="p1">Holydelights is a one-stop shop to plan,organize and manage events. Holydelights support end-to-end management starting with suggesting the most auspicious timings,recommending suitable service providers and providing continuous support until the desired outcome gets delivered.</p>\n<p class="p1">By segregating service at one place for a customer Holydelights has simplified the process for the end consumer to plan,manage and optimize their family events.</p>\n<p class="p1">Holydelights does not discriminate family based upon race,religion,age or language. An online platform is open for those who has a desire to do something special for their family and guests. A complete solution to organize an event for your loved ones.</p>', 1214, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-18 15:29:46', '<p>It is possible that your business has a novel way of solving an existing problem. If this is the case please explain why, in your opinion, is this what the world requires. In what way do the existing solutions not make the grade? Please spell out the innovative nature of your solution. This can be anything from an outstanding breakthrough in medical science or just a mundane item that is common place but impressive nevertheless. This can be a method to iron clothes without the use of electricity or a non-invasive surgery for a critical medical condition. In case your company''s pitch is that it tackles diverse problems faced by the customer then you should discuss these in this space. In such a case amend the heading accordingly and call it Problems instead of Problem.</p><p>While discussing the solutions too you will need to explain clearly how your products or services plan to meet the need of your customer. In case of shortage of parking space your solution might be to offer a rental service for bikes that can be dropped off and picked up at designated spots both near where the students live and where they go to attend their classes. As in the case of Problems, in this case also you may like to reclassify the topic to the use of the plural for Solution in case your plan is to offer solutions to multiple problems.</p>', 'Our Solution', 1),
(1217, 'twyPIdTU', 'Target Market', '', 1213, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Target Market', 'Target Market', 1),
(1218, 'twyPIdTU', 'Market Size & Segments', '<p class="p1">The event industry is one of the fastest growing industry in the country. In India, it is poised to grow at least 25 % annually. A compounded annual growth of 14 per cent, it (event management industry) is projected to be Rs 5,000 crore by 2015 -2016 in the country.</p>\n<p class="p1">Last few years industry have seen that there is a sudden rise of organizing family events hosted by vendors and suppliers. Families residing in tier-1 cities have adopted this mode of scheduling social events and outsourcing to suppliers.</p>\n<p class="p1">As per our recent survey we came to know following:</p><p class="p1">1. An upper-middle-class family spends INR 30 lacs for big events ( for example marriages )</p><p class="p1">2. On an average 10 million ( or 1 crore) events takes place in India every year</p><p class="p1">3. Conservative average of a family event to be ''3 lacs'' i.e 3 trillion for every year.</p><p class="p1">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class="p1">Source: Business Insider &amp; TOI 2014 &amp; 2015 edition</p>', 1217, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-19 13:36:07', '<p>You will now need to discuss your target customers. The questions you will need to find answers to include</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Who are your ideal customers?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Who is the target with problems whose solutions you are offering?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Is it possible to group the customers into cogent segments with respect to needs, locational areas and aspirations? </li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Your reserch should indicate approximate figures in each segment.</li></ul><p>In case you run a gymnasium downtown you may find that different sets of customers may want to use your facility at different times of the day. These sets could be the professionals, the retired people and the college students from the nearby area. Your entire solution must take cognizance of the needs and paying capacities of your customers as well as their requirements in terms of laundry services among others. </p><p>It is important to size your segments. You must assess how lucrative your business in likely to be and this will depend on your customer size in each segment and the paying capcity. If the likely income is inadequate your business might not grow. </p>', 'Market Size & Segments', 1),
(1219, 'twyPIdTU', 'Competition', '', 1213, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Competition', 'Competition', 1),
(1220, 'twyPIdTU', 'Current Alternatives', '<p class="p1">We have not identified competitor with absolutely matching service offerings however there are quite a few in related areas:</p>\n<p class="p1">Wedding specific - weddingz.in,weddingplz.com, wedmegood.com, shaadisaga.com</p>\n<p class="p1">Birthday specific - evibe.in</p>\n<p class="p1">Event - Explara.in</p>\n<p class="p1">Generic listing portals - Urban Clap, Housejoy, Sulekha, JustDial, YellowPages</p>\n<p class="p1">We would be showcasing vendors in a beautiful way and then enable the customers to select the vendors according to their budget. (We have not come across any portal providing both or focusing on family events)</p>', 1219, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-19 13:36:44', '<p>You will need to discuss the competitive environment next. Discuss the kind of competition you have, who these ompetitors are and what are the kinds of solutions they have on offer similar to your solutions. Discuss also why in your opionion the customers might select their solution. </p><p>It is also possible that you may not have any competition in your field. This is fairly common with most of the newer startup innovative companies. The old stalwarts such as Ford did not have any competitors in their field back then. Their customers used whatever state transport was available. Pioneers such as Ford and Sony had to find a way to beat the existing alternatives. Therefore, in case you do not have any competitors just yet, it will still be necessary to debate on the method or methods used by your customers to solve their problem or problems. It is being wise to acknowledge the fact that competition is around the corner even if it is not available right now. You will always need to stay ahead of the race. For this reason you must identify the various advantages you have over all your competitors or alternatives that exist in the market. You will also need to assess whether your products and services enjoy a price advantage in your competitive environment. In case this is not true then you will have to find out why your customers will opt for your solution. The next choice might well be that your solution is better or faster or that your product lasts longer or tastes better. Your outlet might be very conveniently located or your customer service might be better. It is also feasible that your offer suits a certain class of customers.</p>', 'Current Alternatives', 1),
(1221, 'twyPIdTU', 'Our Advantages', '<p class="p1">Holydelights would address one of the major constraints of Family events i.e Budgets.Customers are expected to get influenced if the support includes scheduling to Budgeting.</p>\n<p class="p1">As a late starter, Holydelights have the advantage to incorporate the Best practices from the competitors in terms of design and functionality.</p>\n<p class="p1">In big cities like Kolkata,Mumbai,Delhi, Bangalore, consumer don’t want to spend a time on searching a product or services on stores or showroom. By just one click consumer request services at the home on better cost and quality. Holydelights gives the same feel to the customers by giving full liberty to select events.</p>\n<p class="p1">Major services that can provide competitive edge divided into 3 functionalities:</p>\n<p class="p1">1. Calendar for events (specific to community)</p><p class="p1">2. Providing the vendor listing different categories (corresponding to the event)</p><p class="p1">3. Helping users to conduct their functions within Budget (applicable after a while)</p><p class="p1">Additionally:</p><p class="p1">Both vendors and customers are eligible for various types of interesting Analytics and support hopefully, should keep them engaged.</p>', 1219, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-19 13:37:31', '<p>It is possible that the advantages you have are different for diverse customers. An example could be that of offering expensive notebooks bound in leather as against the cheaper and coarser paper kind available elsewhere. These will be attraxtive to the right kind of customers. When you compare the same product against tablets with software your product may appeal to customers that favour the joy of writing on paper and the absence of need for a cord and power outlet. </p>', 'Our Advantages', 1),
(1222, 'twyPIdTU', 'Execution', '', 0, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Execution', 'Execution', 1),
(1223, 'twyPIdTU', 'Marketing & Sales', '', 1222, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Marketing & Sales', 'Marketing & Sales', 1),
(1224, 'twyPIdTU', 'Marketing Plan', '<p class="p1">Although initial customer acquisition is done through word of mouth but to reach wider target segment we have to adopt Digital Marketing. We would be driving maximum traffic on Holydelights website and promote users to signup for services.</p>\n<p class="p1">We would be covering online marketing channels to capture maximum leads. Below are the steps that will</p>\n<p class="p1">be performed:</p>\n<p class="p1">1) We invest heavily on social media channels to improve the visibility. We will execute search engine</p>\n<p class="p1">optimization technique to improve SERP ( search ranking of a website).</p>\n<p class="p1">2) We implement "Blog Marketing" technique to drive visitors and convert them into leads.</p>\n<p class="p1">3) We start email marketing to bring existing customers back to the online portal while new visitors to</p>\n<p class="p1">signup for the first time to avail the services.</p>\n<p class="p1">Why digital marketing and not traditional forms of marketing? In digital marketing, there are organic ways to grow consumer base without incurring large amounts of money, it has low entry barriers and scale. A lot can be done with less and sharp targeting leading to less wastage.</p>\n<p class="p1">As a startup, how can digital marketing help? It builds awareness and positions Holydelights as a brand. It builds a consistent flow of traffic, gets the first few users. This form of marketing also drive leads and</p>\n<p class="p1">online sales.</p>\n<p class="p1">Keeping the budget constraints in mind, Holydelights need a few techniques/tools that can be used with</p>\n<p class="p1">minimal cost. Let’s look at some of these tools and what can be done to approach these.</p>\n<p class="p1">1.SEO – This is cost-effective with measurable, long-term benefits. It increases the visibility and organic</p>\n<p class="p1">traffic to the website. Using this, there is free branding and it builds trust and credibility. A big advantage</p>\n<p class="p1">is that it opens business 24*7.</p><p class="p1"><br></p><p class="p1">What needs to be done to be SEO friendly? – Have to make website mobile friendly and secure. to ensure all pages are working, using appropriate tags/headers/descriptions. Optimise for faster page load times, create good content on the site, and focus on online PR – get users to talk about the website.</p><p class="p1">2.Content marketing – This generates more traffic, more leads, and builds brand awareness. It also builds the great relationship with current and prospective clients.</p><p class="p1">What to focus on content marketing? – Publish great and relevant content on a regular basis. Formulate</p><p class="p1">unique selling proposition. Set up a blog, tell stories, and work with other publishers to</p><p class="p1">post content/write-ups. Also, communicate customer/consumer stories.</p><p class="p1"><b>3.Social media marketing –</b> This is cost-effective and a platform to build the voice. It is a way to engage with current and future customers. Most popular platforms as per the online business – Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, Google Plus, Tumblr, Pinterest, and Instagram.</p><p class="p1">What shall we do on the platforms? – We will seed the platform with the first few pieces of content. Let the users take over, while we monitor. Use groups/Q&amp;A/chat effectively.</p><p class="p1"><b>4.Email marketing –</b> This is simple, cost-effective, personal, customizable, and measurable with high ROI. We can communicate with an audience of any size. Email has nearly three times as many user accounts as Facebook and Twitter combined.</p><p class="p1">How to go about email marketing? – Identifying a service provider. Common available platforms are : Constant Contact, MailChimp, Aweber, Amazon SES.</p><p class="p1"><b>5.Growth hacking – </b>This is a low-cost and innovative alternative to traditional marketing. How to go about it? – We can offer something for free, set up a referral programme, and go with exclusivity.</p><p class="p1"><br></p>', 1223, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 1, '2016-10-19 13:40:18', '<p>In this space you will need to discuss your marketing plan''s components.</p><ul style=''color:#999''><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>What will be your marketing strategy for the purpose of increasing your customer base? </li><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>Will you invest in SEO, TV time or social media, radio commercial time or in email, signages and digital advertising? </li><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>Do you have or are you planning to have a logo and brand?</li></ul><p>At this stage you will need to select from the above and have estimates and ensure that your forecast includes these figures. </p><p>In case you are planning on advertising, you will need to concentrate on the message you wish to get across. What do you want your USP to be? Is is that you want to vibe with your customers? Discuss how this pitch compares with that of your competitors. Do you want your pitch to be that of a low cost option for those that are consciousof their budget? Or do you wish to project your company''s brand image of a superior product? You may also indicate to your customers that your product is of a special sort such as a solution that is eco-friendly or one that is faster, a solution that is easier and more convenient or one that is locally sourced. Of course all this must be in sync with what you have already committed in the Competitive Landscape Section.</p><p>Discuss your plans of distribution and pricing. What is the manner in which your customers will pay for your products and/or services? Will you expect them to pay at the store or in the field? Or do you want that they should pay at your website? The other options could be payment at the retailers or distribuiters or the resellers. The other point you may clarify is whether your customers are those that buy and use your products or will you sell your products to another company or companies that will include your solution along with theirs? Do you expect that your customers pay up for their purchase each time or will this be a continuous arrantement? There is obviously a fair amount to discuss in this space as can be seen. Additional topics may also be added to this section depending upon the size of your business and its complexity. In such a case it may be more convenient to simply discuss the major points in this space and only refer to all the other points for greater detail. For the smaller businesses however, one can cover all the major issues quite adequately here. </p>', 'Marketing Plan', 1),
(1225, 'twyPIdTU', 'Sales Plan', '', 1223, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>You will need to discuss the manner in which you will sell your products and/or services. It is not necessary to discuss all the activities related to marketing in this space like how you plan to attract all your customers to be. All you need to focus on is how you wish to convert all your likely customers into actuals. These likely customers are those who turn up and ask questions and request for a newsletter and those that ask you for an estimate. So, how do you plan to make all these people your customers. While this may not be too difficult a problem in the smaller businesses it may need a greater degree of working in the case of a business such as insurance or enterprise software where you will need to discuss the finer details of the sales process. In such a case you may need to talk about your staffing needs and whether you have a commission structure. You may discuss your sales territories and quotas or describe the kind of sales activities you will have to use in order to build and maintain your sales process. These may be follow up calls and emails or planning networking events and trade associations as well as referrals among others. </p>', 'Sales Plan', 1),
(1226, 'twyPIdTU', 'Business Operations', '', 1222, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Business Operations', 'Business Operations', 1),
(1227, 'twyPIdTU', 'Locations & Facilities', '', 1226, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>In this space you have to give details of the physical locations of your company. This may well be your office or the place where your store is located or the plants for manufacture or the place where you store all your products. It can be any location that is related to your business. What is the kind of total space you have and how does this relate to the present and future needs of your company? It is quite possible that location is an important factor in your kind of business that may well be a cinema hall or bowling alley or a restaurant. In such a case you will need to explain how the location benefits your business. Are you able to attract a lot of traffic or pedestrians that pass by? Is your location favourable to your target customers? Does your location make it easy for you to run your business such as if it is close to the freeway or a shipping port? Further, in case you operate from home you will need to discuss how this is working well for you or are you thinking of moving out to a new office later on? In case you are,you may give details of when and why. </p>', 'Locations & Facilities', 1),
(1228, 'twyPIdTU', 'Technology', '', 1226, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>Your business may demand the use of some software or hardware or IT tool. You may have been using these tools or may be intending to use them in the future. Please discuss these tools here.</p>', 'Technology', 1),
(1229, 'twyPIdTU', 'Milestones & Metrics', '', 1222, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Milestones & Metrics', 'Milestones & Metrics', 1),
(1230, 'twyPIdTU', 'Milestones', '', 1229, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Milestones', 0),
(1231, 'twyPIdTU', 'Key Metrics', '', 1229, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>In this space you will need to explain the performance parameters that are critical to you.</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">In your perception how do you view success?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">How will you know when you are successful?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">In your view is it critical to keep a check on the direct costs in an industry that works on low margin?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Will you consider your business to be successful if you had adequate leads that help sustain your sales pipeline to its full capacity?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Do you need to have a certain sum of money in your bank for you to feel success?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Are you looking for your website with some flow or see hits being converted into customers?</li></ul><p>Your goal should be to monitor the progress of your plan by continuously tracking the actual results so that you are able to focus on bad assumptions and poor performance quickly enough. This will give you time to do a mid-course correction so that your business remains on track. What you need to do is to find out which of the performance parameters need to be watched with care. </p>', 'Key Metrics', 1),
(1232, 'twyPIdTU', 'Company', '', 0, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Company', 'Company', 1),
(1233, 'twyPIdTU', 'Overview', '', 1232, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Overview', 'Overview', 1),
(1234, 'twyPIdTU', 'Ownership & Structure', '', 1233, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>Here the specifics of the owner or owners have to be explained. While explaining multiple partnerships please mention the percentage share of each in the business. You will also need to discuss the legal structure of your company as to whether it is on the basis of a sole proprietor or it is based on a partnership in the form of a limited liability corporation. It can also be a partnership firm wherein the profits are passed on to individual partners. It can also be a non-profit company or a corporation such as the S type or the  C type with its own tax obligations. It is possible that you are only just beginning and you may not be totally familiar with all these options. In such a case please carry out an online search for various types of business structures and this will give you adequate reading material on the advantages and disadvantages of the different options.</p>', 'Ownership & Structure', 1),
(1235, 'twyPIdTU', 'Team', '', 1232, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Team', 'Team', 1),
(1236, 'twyPIdTU', 'Management Team', '', 1235, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p> For discussing the management team you will need to give the details of the team first. Thereafter, you will need to write out the skills and experience of each team member besides how they will be contributing towards the running of the company business. The details will include the ways in which the members add strength to the company. In case the members have any special qualifications or an experience in the field of interest this will be explained. This space has to be well utilised detailing your strength and that of your team members. If it is true that you have an amazing plan this is where you will show how you are the perfect person to exploit it. In case you are the sole owner of the company, you will have to discuss all your experience and skills as well as the successes you may have had in the past. You may also wish to change the name of this section so that the term of team or team members is avoided since you are the sole proprietor. </p>', 'Management Team', 1),
(1237, 'twyPIdTU', 'Advisors', '', 1235, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>In this space you will discuss all the mentors and investors as well as the professors or the experts from the industry or the subject matter besides friends who are knowledgeable and members of the family among others that have helped you in the business. Give the details of the person or group of persons who you would turn to for advice whenever you have a query or come across a new kind of challenge faced by the business. Explain also the reason why such people are a great help to you and your company. </p>', 'Advisors', 1),
(1238, 'twyPIdTU', 'Financial Plan', '', 0, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Financial Plan', 'Financial Plan', 1),
(1239, 'twyPIdTU', 'Forecast', '', 1238, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Forecast', 'Forecast', 1),
(1240, 'twyPIdTU', 'Key Assumptions', '', 1239, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>Here you will need to justify the values you obtained in your financial forecast. You will need to explain whether you projected your revenue figures by basing these on your past results or market research and a good guess extrapolating from the number of people that visit your store and the percentage of these that may buy or did you use any other method? You will also need to explain the kind of growth that is being assumed, the notable expenditure and the important hires. You may also indicate the level of profit you hope to generate. It will be possible for your readers to see the details of the forecast in your plan. Please make use of this space to create the actual story behind the numbers mentioned. You may also like to indicate the manner in which the financial projections corroborate your conviction that this opportunity is a strong one that is totally deserving of your investment and time. </p>', 'Key Assumptions', 1),
(1241, 'twyPIdTU', 'Revenue', '', 1239, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Revenue', 0),
(1242, 'twyPIdTU', 'Expenses By Year', '', 1239, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Expenses By Year', 0),
(1243, 'twyPIdTU', 'Net Profit and Loss', '', 1239, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Net Profit and Loss', 0),
(1244, 'twyPIdTU', 'Financing', '', 1238, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Financing', 'Financing', 1),
(1245, 'twyPIdTU', 'Use Of funds', '', 1244, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>This space is to be used for you to explain what you propose to do with all forms of financing such as loans and investments that you might have mentioned in your forecast. You may also clarify if these will help cover all the operating costs during the process of scaling up of your new business. You may also explain if this will help finance different forms of capital expenditure that might include the purchase of new and expensive equipment. Please explain to your readers why you will need all these funds and how these will be paid off. However, in case you are not planning on seeking financing please remove this topic. </p>', 'Use Of funds', 1),
(1246, 'twyPIdTU', 'Sources of funds', '', 1244, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '<p>In this space you may please discuss your financing plans. Do you plan to invest your own money? Will you be using a credit card or a line of credit? What are the other kinds of funds do you expect to receive and when do you think you will receive these? Some of these types of funds can be in the form of either personal loan or a business loan and the equity investments that you may receive from others. It is both possible and understandable in case you do not readily have the complete details of the future financing all worked out. All you need to do is to try and explain whatever it is that you know and when you hope to be able to sort out all the details. In case financing is not being sought you may use the space above to give out your plans of bootstrapping your company that is the funding of the growth of the company from its own profits. Alternately, please remove this topic totally from the plan. </p>', 'Sources of funds', 1),
(1247, 'twyPIdTU', 'Statements', '', 1238, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 'Statements', 'Statements', 1),
(1248, 'twyPIdTU', 'Setup Cost', '', 1247, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Setup Cost', 0),
(1249, 'twyPIdTU', 'Income profit and lose', '', 1247, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Income profit and lose', 0),
(1250, 'twyPIdTU', 'Cashflow', '', 1247, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Cashflow', 0),
(1251, 'twyPIdTU', 'Balance Sheet', '', 1247, 1, 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', 31, '2016-10-17 14:07:05', '', 'Balance Sheet', 0),
(1252, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Business Summary', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Business Summary', 'Business Summary', 1),
(1253, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Business Opportunity', '', 1252, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Business Opportunity', 'Business Opportunity', 1),
(1254, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Problem Description', '', 1253, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>Here you need to make a summary of what had been written in the Problem Statement section. The summary should consist of what all is required by your customers which they cannot find anywhere else. Your business need not be unique but you will need to specify those reasons that justify the existence of your business. It is possible that the location you have selected is excellent or your pricing has an edge over the other competitors. It is important to appreciate that only once you have addressed all the details should you attempt to write out the executive summary. </p>', 'Problem Description', 1),
(1255, 'gSlBkJzD', 'The Solution', '', 1253, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>Here you will need to make a summary of whatever was written in The Solution section. The prominent questions that need to be answered are (a) What is your solution to the customer''s problems and (b) Why are your products or services so critically important for them?</p>', 'The Solution', 1),
(1256, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Market Opportunity', '', 1253, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>Make an incisive summary of Market Opportunity section. Offer a good interpretation of your idea of an ideal customer. Also specify the number of potential customers you are likely to have for the solution you have in mind. See if you can find a yardstick with which you can group your customers into discrete types. </p>', 'Market Opportunity', 1),
(1257, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Competitive Landscape', '', 1253, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>You will need to make a summary of what had been written in the Competitive Landscape section. Make a list of the various options that your customers have for their problems and in what way is the solutionn offered by you better than these. </p>', 'Competitive Landscape', 1),
(1258, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Why us?', '', 1253, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>Provide a summary of the Company Name section. Here you will need to spell out all those points that favour the selection of your company in preference to the other competitors. Some of these points will include the skills and experience of your team members. In what ways are the business acumen and the industry connections better in your team mates? How do they excel in matters such as innovations or industry connections and expertise in the subject matter? What sort of professional competence do your key advisors possess? </p>', 'Why us?', 1),
(1259, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Business Expectations', '', 1252, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Business Expectations', 'Business Expectations', 1),
(1260, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Financial Projections', '', 1259, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>In this space you will need to make a summary of your financial goals. You will have to specify the kind of revenue you think you are likely to make within the first year of the busness. Further, you will need to mention the type of revenue growth you expect within the coming years. An important estimate you will have to provide deals with the profitability expectation for your business. How soon do you expect to break even and start making profits?You may need to specify the reason in case you plan to run your business as a loss making venture. Here, the details you will provide will also include the important metrics that would bear watching. The projected financial statements may well be seen by your readers later on. Your endeavour should be to heighten the interest of your readers to learn more in respect of your company by using this space to review the various highlights of the forecast you have prepared. </p>', 'Financial Projections', 1),
(1261, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Financing Required', '', 1259, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>The section Financial Projections will need to be summarized.</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">How will you finance your business?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Will you need financing from extraneous sources or do you have adequate finances or is it already fully self sufficient? It is up to you to either remove the section or make a note in case you do not need financing from outside sources. </li></ul>', 'Financing Required', 1),
(1262, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Business Opportunity', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Business Opportunity', 'Business Opportunity', 1),
(1263, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Problem & Solution', '', 1262, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Problem & Solution', 'Problem & Solution', 1);
INSERT INTO `plan_menu` (`menuid`, `companyid`, `title`, `summary`, `parentid`, `status`, `createdby`, `createdon`, `modifiedby`, `modifiedon`, `content`, `hidden_title`, `permission`) VALUES
(1264, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Problem worth solving', '', 1263, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>Your customers may have a key problem or a need that has not been met. If your line of business is the common type such as a beauty parlour or a restaurant, please explain as to why your customers have a need to frequent the parlour or the eating joing. Is it because your place is cheaper or because you maintain hours that are convenient to your patrons? Is your place situated at a good location or do you meet a necessity that is otherwise not available in your neck of the woods? Such an example could be a late night Latte Coffee Bar or a sandwich bar that is open till the wee hours of the night.</p>', 'Problem worth solving', 1),
(1265, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Our Solution', '', 1263, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>It is possible that your business has a novel way of solving an existing problem. If this is the case please explain why, in your opinion, is this what the world requires. In what way do the existing solutions not make the grade? Please spell out the innovative nature of your solution. This can be anything from an outstanding breakthrough in medical science or just a mundane item that is common place but impressive nevertheless. This can be a method to iron clothes without the use of electricity or a non-invasive surgery for a critical medical condition. In case your company''s pitch is that it tackles diverse problems faced by the customer then you should discuss these in this space. In such a case amend the heading accordingly and call it Problems instead of Problem.</p><p>While discussing the solutions too you will need to explain clearly how your products or services plan to meet the need of your customer. In case of shortage of parking space your solution might be to offer a rental service for bikes that can be dropped off and picked up at designated spots both near where the students live and where they go to attend their classes. As in the case of Problems, in this case also you may like to reclassify the topic to the use of the plural for Solution in case your plan is to offer solutions to multiple problems.</p>', 'Our Solution', 1),
(1266, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Target Market', '', 1262, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Target Market', 'Target Market', 1),
(1267, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Market Size & Segments', '', 1266, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>You will now need to discuss your target customers. The questions you will need to find answers to include</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Who are your ideal customers?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Who is the target with problems whose solutions you are offering?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> Is it possible to group the customers into cogent segments with respect to needs, locational areas and aspirations? </li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Your reserch should indicate approximate figures in each segment.</li></ul><p>In case you run a gymnasium downtown you may find that different sets of customers may want to use your facility at different times of the day. These sets could be the professionals, the retired people and the college students from the nearby area. Your entire solution must take cognizance of the needs and paying capacities of your customers as well as their requirements in terms of laundry services among others. </p><p>It is important to size your segments. You must assess how lucrative your business in likely to be and this will depend on your customer size in each segment and the paying capcity. If the likely income is inadequate your business might not grow. </p>', 'Market Size & Segments', 1),
(1268, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Competition', '', 1262, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Competition', 'Competition', 1),
(1269, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Current Alternatives', '', 1268, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>You will need to discuss the competitive environment next. Discuss the kind of competition you have, who these ompetitors are and what are the kinds of solutions they have on offer similar to your solutions. Discuss also why in your opionion the customers might select their solution. </p><p>It is also possible that you may not have any competition in your field. This is fairly common with most of the newer startup innovative companies. The old stalwarts such as Ford did not have any competitors in their field back then. Their customers used whatever state transport was available. Pioneers such as Ford and Sony had to find a way to beat the existing alternatives. Therefore, in case you do not have any competitors just yet, it will still be necessary to debate on the method or methods used by your customers to solve their problem or problems. It is being wise to acknowledge the fact that competition is around the corner even if it is not available right now. You will always need to stay ahead of the race. For this reason you must identify the various advantages you have over all your competitors or alternatives that exist in the market. You will also need to assess whether your products and services enjoy a price advantage in your competitive environment. In case this is not true then you will have to find out why your customers will opt for your solution. The next choice might well be that your solution is better or faster or that your product lasts longer or tastes better. Your outlet might be very conveniently located or your customer service might be better. It is also feasible that your offer suits a certain class of customers.</p>', 'Current Alternatives', 1),
(1270, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Our Advantages', '', 1268, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>It is possible that the advantages you have are different for diverse customers. An example could be that of offering expensive notebooks bound in leather as against the cheaper and coarser paper kind available elsewhere. These will be attraxtive to the right kind of customers. When you compare the same product against tablets with software your product may appeal to customers that favour the joy of writing on paper and the absence of need for a cord and power outlet. </p>', 'Our Advantages', 1),
(1271, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Execution', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Execution', 'Execution', 1),
(1272, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Marketing & Sales', '', 1271, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Marketing & Sales', 'Marketing & Sales', 1),
(1273, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Marketing Plan', '', 1272, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>In this space you will need to discuss your marketing plan''s components.</p><ul style=''color:#999''><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>What will be your marketing strategy for the purpose of increasing your customer base? </li><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>Will you invest in SEO, TV time or social media, radio commercial time or in email, signages and digital advertising? </li><li style=''list-style-type: lower-alpha;''>Do you have or are you planning to have a logo and brand?</li></ul><p>At this stage you will need to select from the above and have estimates and ensure that your forecast includes these figures. </p><p>In case you are planning on advertising, you will need to concentrate on the message you wish to get across. What do you want your USP to be? Is is that you want to vibe with your customers? Discuss how this pitch compares with that of your competitors. Do you want your pitch to be that of a low cost option for those that are consciousof their budget? Or do you wish to project your company''s brand image of a superior product? You may also indicate to your customers that your product is of a special sort such as a solution that is eco-friendly or one that is faster, a solution that is easier and more convenient or one that is locally sourced. Of course all this must be in sync with what you have already committed in the Competitive Landscape Section.</p><p>Discuss your plans of distribution and pricing. What is the manner in which your customers will pay for your products and/or services? Will you expect them to pay at the store or in the field? Or do you want that they should pay at your website? The other options could be payment at the retailers or distribuiters or the resellers. The other point you may clarify is whether your customers are those that buy and use your products or will you sell your products to another company or companies that will include your solution along with theirs? Do you expect that your customers pay up for their purchase each time or will this be a continuous arrantement? There is obviously a fair amount to discuss in this space as can be seen. Additional topics may also be added to this section depending upon the size of your business and its complexity. In such a case it may be more convenient to simply discuss the major points in this space and only refer to all the other points for greater detail. For the smaller businesses however, one can cover all the major issues quite adequately here. </p>', 'Marketing Plan', 1),
(1274, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Sales Plan', '', 1272, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>You will need to discuss the manner in which you will sell your products and/or services. It is not necessary to discuss all the activities related to marketing in this space like how you plan to attract all your customers to be. All you need to focus on is how you wish to convert all your likely customers into actuals. These likely customers are those who turn up and ask questions and request for a newsletter and those that ask you for an estimate. So, how do you plan to make all these people your customers. While this may not be too difficult a problem in the smaller businesses it may need a greater degree of working in the case of a business such as insurance or enterprise software where you will need to discuss the finer details of the sales process. In such a case you may need to talk about your staffing needs and whether you have a commission structure. You may discuss your sales territories and quotas or describe the kind of sales activities you will have to use in order to build and maintain your sales process. These may be follow up calls and emails or planning networking events and trade associations as well as referrals among others. </p>', 'Sales Plan', 1),
(1275, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Business Operations', '', 1271, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Business Operations', 'Business Operations', 1),
(1276, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Locations & Facilities', '', 1275, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>In this space you have to give details of the physical locations of your company. This may well be your office or the place where your store is located or the plants for manufacture or the place where you store all your products. It can be any location that is related to your business. What is the kind of total space you have and how does this relate to the present and future needs of your company? It is quite possible that location is an important factor in your kind of business that may well be a cinema hall or bowling alley or a restaurant. In such a case you will need to explain how the location benefits your business. Are you able to attract a lot of traffic or pedestrians that pass by? Is your location favourable to your target customers? Does your location make it easy for you to run your business such as if it is close to the freeway or a shipping port? Further, in case you operate from home you will need to discuss how this is working well for you or are you thinking of moving out to a new office later on? In case you are,you may give details of when and why. </p>', 'Locations & Facilities', 1),
(1277, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Technology', '', 1275, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>Your business may demand the use of some software or hardware or IT tool. You may have been using these tools or may be intending to use them in the future. Please discuss these tools here.</p>', 'Technology', 1),
(1278, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Milestones & Metrics', '', 1271, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Milestones & Metrics', 'Milestones & Metrics', 1),
(1279, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Milestones', '', 1278, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '', 'Milestones', 0),
(1280, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Key Metrics', '', 1278, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>In this space you will need to explain the performance parameters that are critical to you.</p><ul style="color:#999"><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">In your perception how do you view success?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">How will you know when you are successful?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">In your view is it critical to keep a check on the direct costs in an industry that works on low margin?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Will you consider your business to be successful if you had adequate leads that help sustain your sales pipeline to its full capacity?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Do you need to have a certain sum of money in your bank for you to feel success?</li><li style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">Are you looking for your website with some flow or see hits being converted into customers?</li></ul><p>Your goal should be to monitor the progress of your plan by continuously tracking the actual results so that you are able to focus on bad assumptions and poor performance quickly enough. This will give you time to do a mid-course correction so that your business remains on track. What you need to do is to find out which of the performance parameters need to be watched with care. </p>', 'Key Metrics', 1),
(1281, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Company', '', 0, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Company', 'Company', 1),
(1282, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Overview', '', 1281, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Overview', 'Overview', 1),
(1283, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Ownership & Structure', '', 1282, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>Here the specifics of the owner or owners have to be explained. While explaining multiple partnerships please mention the percentage share of each in the business. You will also need to discuss the legal structure of your company as to whether it is on the basis of a sole proprietor or it is based on a partnership in the form of a limited liability corporation. It can also be a partnership firm wherein the profits are passed on to individual partners. It can also be a non-profit company or a corporation such as the S type or the  C type with its own tax obligations. It is possible that you are only just beginning and you may not be totally familiar with all these options. In such a case please carry out an online search for various types of business structures and this will give you adequate reading material on the advantages and disadvantages of the different options.</p>', 'Ownership & Structure', 1),
(1284, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Team', '', 1281, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 'Team', 'Team', 1),
(1285, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Management Team', '', 1284, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p> For discussing the management team you will need to give the details of the team first. Thereafter, you will need to write out the skills and experience of each team member besides how they will be contributing towards the running of the company business. The details will include the ways in which the members add strength to the company. In case the members have any special qualifications or an experience in the field of interest this will be explained. This space has to be well utilised detailing your strength and that of your team members. If it is true that you have an amazing plan this is where you will show how you are the perfect person to exploit it. In case you are the sole owner of the company, you will have to discuss all your experience and skills as well as the successes you may have had in the past. You may also wish to change the name of this section so that the term of team or team members is avoided since you are the sole proprietor. </p>', 'Management Team', 1),
(1286, 'gSlBkJzD', 'Advisors', '', 1284, 1, 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', 29, '2016-10-17 14:09:04', '<p>In this space you will discuss all the mentors and investors as well as the professors or the experts from the industry or the subject matter besides friends who are knowledgeable and members of the family among others that have helped you in the business. Give the details of the person or group of persons who you would turn to for advice whenever you have a query or come across a new kind of challenge faced by the business. Explain also the reason why such people are a great help to you and your company. </p>', 'Advisors', 1),
